1
00:00:02,127 --> 00:00:02,920
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,920 --> 00:00:03,170
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:06,632
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:10,677
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:10,886 --> 00:00:11,887
(QUACKS)

6
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:13,764
Adventure Time

7
00:00:13,931 --> 00:00:15,307
Come on, grab your friends

8
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:17,768
We'll go to very distant lands

9
00:00:18,143 --> 00:00:20,270
With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

10
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:21,980
The fun will never end

11
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:23,607
It's Adventure Time

12
00:00:31,782 --> 00:00:33,200
(VIDEO GAME MUSIC PLAYS)

13
00:00:33,909 --> 00:00:37,287
Beemo, I've been playing
this 72 hours straight.

14
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:39,831
Can I please save after this battle?

15
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:43,043
No, it takes up too much brain space.

16
00:00:44,336 --> 00:00:45,837
I'm out of candles. Huh?

17
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,174
Man, if Finn were here,
we'd be doing this in shifts.

18
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:50,842
Oh, well, let's keep grinding.

19
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:53,470
I cannot talk and run this game
at the same time.

20
00:00:55,472 --> 00:00:56,807
No!

21
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:58,976
Well, I guess that means I'm free.

22
00:00:59,351 --> 00:01:01,228
I live again!

23
00:01:01,979 --> 00:01:04,314
My name is Jake, and love my life

24
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:07,067
Kissin' on lady 'cause
she's basically my wife

25
00:01:07,568 --> 00:01:09,778
Fixin' up Neptr 'cause he fell from a tree

26
00:01:10,279 --> 00:01:13,073
Catchin' up with Maja and Aptwe

27
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:16,535
Maja's in a coma, and she might not wake up

28
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:19,329
I'm glad you got a friend now
even though that's messed up

29
00:01:19,705 --> 00:01:22,332
Take T. V. To the market to get him into fruits

30
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:26,169
Take a little nappy in my blanket cocoon

31
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:29,214
Wake up really early just to cook
for my friends

32
00:01:29,423 --> 00:01:31,717
Later in the field at night
I thought I saw death

33
00:01:32,175 --> 00:01:34,469
Made myself a boat, and I sailed with a whale

34
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,681
Took T. V. To the market so he could try kale

35
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:40,475
And some other stuff

36
00:01:40,976 --> 00:01:42,060
Ah!

37
00:01:42,311 --> 00:01:43,312
Nice song, Jake.

38
00:01:43,604 --> 00:01:44,980
What a crazy two weeks.

39
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:48,358
I think I'm ready to hole up
and go round two on Age of Grinders.

40
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:51,194
But where's Finn?
I need him on this adventure.

41
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:53,238
Uh, well...

42
00:01:53,697 --> 00:01:55,616
Hold on. What?

43
00:01:56,241 --> 00:01:58,744
If you don't know, I'm not sure
it's my business to tell you.

44
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:02,372
Don't you dare, Shelby!
Give up that greasy gossip!

45
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:07,628
Word on the street is,
Finn's been hangin' with a new lady.

46
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:11,173
Who the honk is it?

47
00:02:11,298 --> 00:02:13,133
- I don't...
- Muscle Princess. It's perfect.

48
00:02:13,425 --> 00:02:14,926
- I don't...
- Me-Mow, from the future!

49
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:16,511
- (GASPS)
- Nobody knows.

50
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:19,431
Finn's been keeping this on the super DL.

51
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:22,059
- Why?
- He's just trying to be careful this time.

52
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:23,810
Oh, yeah, I get it.

53
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:25,937
But, I still got to know who this girl is.

54
00:02:26,021 --> 00:02:27,439
Okay, just don't blow up his spot.

55
00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:29,316
JAKE: T won't!

56
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:30,692
Ooh! Ohhh!

57
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:33,779
- Hey, Jake.
- Oh, hey, Science Cat.

58
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:35,072
Where's Sword Shark?

59
00:02:35,322 --> 00:02:36,448
He died of old age.

60
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:39,326
Hey, are you gonna find out
who Finn's girlfriend is?

61
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:40,661
Who told you that?

62
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:42,329
Word gets around, man.

63
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:44,081
Not to me, apparently.

64
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:45,791
Let me know the dirt when you find out.

65
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:46,833
I won'tl!

66
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:49,336
(SNIFFING)

67
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:50,962
(FLUTE PLAYING)

68
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:52,422
Huh? What's that?

69
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:55,592
Sounds like a flute
coming from above the canopy.

70
00:02:57,594 --> 00:02:58,595
(FLUTE CONTINUES)

71
00:02:58,845 --> 00:02:59,930
(GASPS)

72
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:06,603
Huntress Wizard!

73
00:03:07,354 --> 00:03:08,480
- Stop.
- (PLAYING STOPS)

74
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,358
This isn't working, Finn.

75
00:03:15,487 --> 00:03:16,988
- Dude.
- (SCREAMS)

76
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:19,199
Oh, hi, Jake. What are you doing here?

77
00:03:19,491 --> 00:03:21,493
I wanted to check out your new lady friend,

78
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:25,080
but I guess she just dumped you
like a diaper in the dirt, bro.

79
00:03:25,706 --> 00:03:27,958
(CRYING) I'm sorry, man.

80
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:32,003
I want you to have a healthy relationship
with someone cool.

81
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:34,881
That's so sweet, Jake. I love you, man.

82
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:36,133
Me, too, man.

83
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:37,759
Okay. I'm okay.

84
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:40,220
But, dude, me and Huntress Wizard
weren't together.

85
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:43,390
We're just trying to conjure up
the Spirit of the Forest with my flute spell.

86
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,642
What the blood are you talking about?

87
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,269
It went down like this.

88
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:49,604
I was just minding my own business

89
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,481
in my new alone place I've been
hanging out at.

90
00:03:51,523 --> 00:03:52,899
(GURGLING)

91
00:03:54,151 --> 00:03:55,152
(FLUTE PLAYING)

92
00:03:57,487 --> 00:03:58,530
(BLOWING RASPBERRY)

93
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:01,032
- Hello.
- How are you playing like that?

94
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:03,285
I don't know. I'm just making stuff up.

95
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:07,664
Something in your notes has the quality
of a powerful evocation spell.

96
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:09,541
What spirit guides your hands?

97
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:11,752
Tell me, or I'll put this up your nose.

98
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:13,670
First off, I'm a great fighter.

99
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:16,256
And I'm especially agile
when I'm nude, so good luck.

100
00:04:16,757 --> 00:04:19,134
Second, my flute improv ain't no secret.

101
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,470
I let my grass hand do whatever it wants,

102
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:23,722
which is usually sort of shreddy and busy.

103
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:25,599
Let me see that hand.

104
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:29,227
You're what I've been looking for.

105
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:32,022
Lookin' for a dope boyfriend.

106
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:34,274
No, man,
she thinks my grass arm flute playing

107
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:35,901
could summon the Spirit of the Forest.

108
00:04:36,151 --> 00:04:39,279
I've been playing different songs for two
weeks, though, and he hasn't shown up yet.

109
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:40,906
Who's that, her ex-boyfriend?

110
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:43,158
Uh, I guess they used to hang out

111
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:46,286
but maybe in some kind
of mentor-student capacity.

112
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:49,372
So my theory holds.
You can still make this happen.

113
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,917
Yeah, I really want to help
her summon this dude.

114
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,418
Finn, that's not why you're here.

115
00:04:53,752 --> 00:04:54,920
That's why I'm here.

116
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:56,630
Come on, let's make some magic happen.

117
00:04:57,047 --> 00:04:58,548
Yeah, my magic flute spell.

118
00:05:02,803 --> 00:05:04,054
(GROANS)

119
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,263
- HUNTRESS WIZARD: Finn.
- (BOTH SCREAM)

120
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:06,431
I had an idea.

121
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:08,016
Hi.

122
00:05:08,058 --> 00:05:09,810
I think the problem is your flute.

123
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,437
We should make you a better
one from a magical tusk.

124
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:15,565
Like the tusk of the legendary Thunder Boar
that lives in these woods.

125
00:05:16,024 --> 00:05:17,317
I'm down for whatever if it helps.

126
00:05:17,776 --> 00:05:18,819
I'm also here.

127
00:05:19,194 --> 00:05:20,195
Hey, what's up?

128
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:23,698
It's late. Why don't you guys
crash at my place tonight?

129
00:05:23,949 --> 00:05:25,325
We'll start the hunt first thing in the morning.

130
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:29,162
Ha-ha! I'm like your sleepover chaperone.

131
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:31,331
- Grow up.
- You grow up, you teen!

132
00:05:37,546 --> 00:05:39,464
So, yeah, here's the place.

133
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:42,092
We got some nice soft dirt right over here.

134
00:05:42,217 --> 00:05:44,719
Pantry, in case you want a snack, bathroom.

135
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,721
I got a console if you get bored,

136
00:05:46,972 --> 00:05:48,974
but it was a gift,
so I haven't really set it up yet.

137
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:50,684
Night, boys.

138
00:05:59,109 --> 00:06:00,485
(SNORES)

139
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:02,988
JAKE: Dude, I think I figured it out.

140
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:06,867
You can't summon the Spirit of the Forest
‘cause you ain't playing that flute for him.

141
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,743
You got a crush on HW.

142
00:06:08,994 --> 00:06:11,621
HW's just training me to live
an ascetic life like her.

143
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:14,249
Mmm, okay, I buy that for like zero seconds.

144
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:27,762
Before we hunt the Thunder Boar,
you should drink from this enchanted spring.

145
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,140
It might give you crazy dreams,

146
00:06:30,265 --> 00:06:33,351
but when you wake up, you'll be immune
to the Boar's electrical attacks.

147
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,645
Let's roll those dice. (GULPING)

148
00:06:36,021 --> 00:06:37,731
Hey, dude, are you sure you want to do that?

149
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:39,107
Mm-hmm. Blah!

150
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:42,027
I've had plenty of weird dreams... Okay!

151
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:43,403
That was fast. (CHIRPS)

152
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:50,410
Welcome. I am the Spirit of the Forest.

153
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:54,915
Wow, dude, we've been trying
to summon you for weeks.

154
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,416
And why do you seek me?

155
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,543
I don't, personally,

156
00:06:58,543 --> 00:07:00,795
but Huntress Wizard really wants
to talk to you, man.

157
00:07:00,921 --> 00:07:03,882
Did you know that a wolf's eyes
are on the front of its head?

158
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:05,884
But, yeah, didn't you guys used to hang?

159
00:07:06,176 --> 00:07:08,261
Most predatory species are like that.

160
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:10,263
This little buddy doesn't even know I'm here.

161
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:12,766
Fella, I don't want to have
a science talk right now.

162
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:15,518
Huntress Wizard only sees straight ahead.

163
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:17,020
Eyes on the prize.

164
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:19,189
Now, why did you really need to see me?

165
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:22,150
Oh, yeah!
Can you make me immune to electricity?

166
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,777
- Here.
- Whoa.

167
00:07:24,069 --> 00:07:25,695
Now plunge that into your heart.

168
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,949
And this'll give me immunity to electricity?

169
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:33,203
I'll do it. To help Huntress Wizard.

170
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:36,581
(YELLS)

171
00:07:36,957 --> 00:07:37,958
How long was I out?

172
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:39,793
Seven long, harrowing seconds.

173
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:41,086
Hold still.

174
00:07:41,586 --> 00:07:42,587
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

175
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:44,714
- FINN: Yeah, feels fine.
- Great.

176
00:07:45,048 --> 00:07:46,591
Now we can hunt down the Thunder Boar.

177
00:07:47,092 --> 00:07:48,218
Oh, yeah, the Boar.

178
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:49,928
Try to stay focused.

179
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:54,432
Magic dog, what do you smell?

180
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:55,600
(SNIFFS)

181
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:58,937
Mostly, Finn but also some
kind of giant wild pig.

182
00:07:59,104 --> 00:08:00,105
There!

183
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:03,608
(GRUNTS)

184
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:06,111
(SQUEALING)

185
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:08,738
Jake's joking. I smell fine.

186
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:12,993
(GRUNTS)

187
00:08:18,707 --> 00:08:19,749
(SNICKERING)

188
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,377
Hey!

189
00:08:22,836 --> 00:08:23,837
Good work.

190
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:25,630
You just wanted a tusk?

191
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,633
- You could have asked!
- Oh.

192
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:35,306
(INHALES SHARPLY)

193
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:36,891
(FLUTE PLAYING)

194
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:48,069
You can stop.

195
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:49,821
He is not coming.

196
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:52,949
He's gone for good, and I should just deal.

197
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:56,077
Maybe if I played it a little jazzier,
like, all syncopated?

198
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:58,580
Hey! Why don't you two try playing together?

199
00:08:58,830 --> 00:09:00,540
Use that chemistry to guide the music.

200
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:02,959
Yeah, just get in there. Cozy up.

201
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:05,336
I guess we've tried everything else.

202
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,964
(FLUTES PLAYING)

203
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:13,219
Wow!

204
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:15,472
What?

205
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:19,350
Who summons me with the sweet song
of longing?

206
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:22,062
Oh, hey-oh. Can you see me now?

207
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:24,230
- Yes.
- SPIRIT: How's it been going?

208
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:26,066
I've been talking to a lot of twigs.

209
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:28,860
- Where have you been, dude?
- I've been right here.

210
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:32,197
But the forces that drew us close
became obscured

211
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:35,241
as you drifted into the
lifestyles of magic city livin'.

212
00:09:35,825 --> 00:09:38,703
Attracting forces come and go.
It's the way of the world.

213
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,122
I still can't tell if you guys dated.

214
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:43,124
But I'm ready to come back now.

215
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,376
- Are you, though?
- That's what I'm saying.

216
00:09:45,877 --> 00:09:47,879
Finn, who was your flute spell for?

217
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:50,507
Um...

218
00:09:51,883 --> 00:09:53,760
I was playing my flute for you the whole time,

219
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:57,388
but I knew you had a thing with this dude,
and he seems cool,

220
00:09:58,014 --> 00:10:00,141
so I was just gonna keep playing
this flute song

221
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:02,352
about my secret feelings until my flute broke.

222
00:10:03,228 --> 00:10:07,148
I, uh, I worry that hard meat don't get eat.

223
00:10:07,482 --> 00:10:10,026
That is to say,
if I ever find what I'm looking for,

224
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:12,737
I'll become soft and I'll cease
to matter in this world.

225
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:13,863
What?

226
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:17,283
Fear of softness is what drove me
to the mad and sad world of wizarding.

227
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:19,744
- And, Finn...
- Yeah? What?

228
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:22,413
(GASPS)

229
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:25,416
My flute spell was for you, too.

230
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:27,544
You're an exceptional beast,
and you have great hair.

231
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:31,047
But exceptional beasts
like us cannot fall in love.

232
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:33,383
That is the secret of ordinary people.

233
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:35,176
Uh, that's real dumb.

234
00:10:35,677 --> 00:10:36,678
I agree.

235
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:38,388
Wait, you agree with me or her?

236
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:42,183
Take it easy, Huntress Wizard.

237
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:47,564
FINN: Man, I can't believe all you can do
is upgrade your armor in this game.

238
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:49,274
It's all about patience

239
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:53,820
and treating each grueling,
repetitive battle as if it were your first.

240
00:10:54,445 --> 00:10:55,530
FINN: Oh, snap!

241
00:10:56,573 --> 00:10:57,574
Finally!

242
00:10:57,824 --> 00:10:58,950
BOTH: Whoo!

243
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:00,160
BOTH: Blah!

244
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:03,079
What a bad and boring game.
It was just what I needed.

245
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:05,540
I'm sorry it didn't work out
with Huntress Wizard.

246
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:08,168
She just needs time to miss how cool you are.

247
00:11:08,585 --> 00:11:10,211
Attracting forces come and go, man.

248
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:12,463
(SINGLE NOTE PLAYS)

249
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:17,844
Come along with me

250
00:11:18,970 --> 00:11:22,849
And the butterflies and bees

251
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:27,979
This party is so crazy!

